    "Research on explainable content recommendation systems has been done from multiple perspectives, including contentbased and collaborative filtering methods (Bilgic & Mooney, 2005) as the two most prevalent bases for recommendation systems.",
    "Researchers have been continuously focusing on improving the user experience.",
    "For example, scientists have investigated the comprehensibility of artificial intelligence (AI) systems and their effect on user satisfaction within the scope of context-aware intelligent systems (Lim et al., 2009).",
    "The researchers investigated the comprehensibility of several context-aware systems and how users engage with them.",
    "At the same time, researchers examined the effects of counterfactual explanations on the understanding of recommendations from the perspective of end users."
